EmailTemplate.subject: You are invited to our 2018 'With Love' Gala in Winnipeg!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
As our little learners from Ecole L’Union are on summer break, we’re working hard behind the scenes, planning for our upcoming fundraising gala. Last year's was a fantastic success, and as we have big plans for combating trafficking in Haiti, this year's gala will play a significant role in creating more awareness and raising support.
Our “With Love” gala is happening on October 4th at the Canadian Museum for Human Rights in Winnipeg, Manitoba, and will benefit both our work in Haiti and here at home in Canada! It’s an evening of great food, entertainment, and important stories, all in support of our work against the exploitation of young girls in Haiti and providing Canadian students with a positive message of hope, encouragement, and purpose.
If it’s possible, we’d love to have you join us for this special occasion. For more information on purchasing individual tickets or a table, visit livedifferent.com/with-love-gala.
Thank you for your continued support of the life-changing work that we’re already doing in Haiti!
All the best,
Ashley Smart Director of Operations Live Different ashley@livedifferent.com (866) 432 4464 ext. 212
